parameters:
Clea (The fog is so thick... We can't see even a little
ahead. If we get attacked here, we'll be wiped out
immediately. It's better to turn back.)

Clea (No, today we won't waste this opportunity. We'll
settle things right here...!)
Nora the Thief: Ah... Ahh... The voice of a dragon...!!

Mage Relm: Ugh... This tingling sensation... This is a
dragon, a real dragon...!

Priestess Sophia: Look ahead! The fog is moving, something
is approaching us!!

Clea: It seems like we were not fighting a dragon, but this
girl instead...

Priestess Sophia: Clea-chan, since when did you realize that
there was no dragon?

Clea: It was when I heard the voice of the dragon. It was
much more ominous and evil.

Clea: What I heard here was not just anger... but a voice
filled with even more sadness.

Priestess Sophia: We can't just leave this girl here. Let's
take her with us to the village.
Priestess Sophia: I'm glad, you've woken up.
Clea: My name is Clea, what's yours?

Phoni: I am Phoni... I see... I have lost to all of you,
haven't I?
Clea: Can you tell me about you and the dragon?

Phoni: This is a story from a few months ago. A dragon came
to this mountain.

Phoni: The beasts that were frightened by the dragon started
coming down the mountain, and the village suffered
devastating damage.

Phoni: Various things were offered: food, treasures,
livestock, and even me, the village's priestess.

Priestess Phoni: I am called the Voice Priestess. I can use
magic to reproduce any sound I have heard before.

Mage Relm: Lost Magic...! The Devil's Magic of Sound
Projection, Kowon's Magic!!
Mage Relm: Th-th-this is an incredible discovery!

Priestess Sophia: The reason I was wary of the Magic Academy
was because I was afraid of the discovery of Lost Magic.

Clea: I understand that you were able to reproduce the voice
of the dragon, but what was the reason for pretending to be
the dragon?

Village Chief Olden: Phoni, Phoni!! I'm glad I can never see
you again--
Voice Priestess Phoni: Please don't come!!

Voice Priestess Phoni: I was dedicated to you, Father. I was
told to die for the sake of the village and become a
sacrifice!

Voice Priestess Phoni: That's why I wanted to seek revenge!
Against the village that offered me as a sacrifice,
pretending to be a dragon!

Voice Priestess Phoni: Please tell me, Father... the way to
love the one who killed me... ugh...
